BRUCELLOSIS, PORCINE - GERMANY: (MECKLENBURG-WESTERN POMERANIA), SEROVAR 2
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Mon 22 Sep 2008
From: Thomas Mettenleiter <Thomas.Mettenleiter@fli.bund.de>


Responsible veterinary authorities imposed restrictions on a farm
after positive serological results in outdoor farmed pigs. The sera
were collected during a voluntary monitoring for this disease.

Further serological and bacteriological examinations confirmed the
diagnosis of brucellosis. Bacteriological differentiation performed
at the National Reference Laboratory at the
Friedrich-Loeffler-Institut identified the agent as _Brucella suis_
biovar 2. The pigs in question were culled and removed in agreement
with sanitary regulations.

_Brucella suis_ biovar 2 is the cause of porcine brucellosis in
Central Europe. In contrast to _Brucella suis_ biovar 1 and biovar 3,
biovar 2 is assumed to be pathogenic for humans only under certain
circumstances, i.e. long-term immunosuppressive treatment.
Nevertheless, sanitary regulations as outlined in the German animal
disease legislation also apply to pigs infected with _Brucella suis_ biovar 2.

Biovar 2 of _Brucella suis_ is present in wild boars and hares in
Germany as shown by a serological survey (Melzer et al., 2006).
Various isolations of this agent in the last few years from both
animal species confirmed this finding.

How the pathogen was introduced into the farm has not been elucidated
so far. The local state veterinarian acknowledged that this outdoor
farm operates according to the rules. Three brucellosis outbreaks
have been notified up to now in Germany in 2008. All were registered
in Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania. Germany is officially free of
brucellosis in cattle, sheep and goats.

--
Prof. Dr. rer. nat. habil. Dr. med. vet. h.c. Thomas C. Mettenleiter
Praesident und Professor
Friedrich-Loeffler-Institut
17493 Greifswald-Insel Riems
Germany
<Thomas.Mettenleiter@fli.bund.de>

